Project 1: Local Library Mobile App
Test Documentation Suite

1. Test Plan Document

Document ID: TPL-LIB-APP-001
Version: 1.0
Date: October 26, 2023*

Section	Details
1.0 Introduction	This document outlines the test strategy, objectives, and schedule for the initial release of the "Community Library" mobile application (v1.0).

2.0 Test Objectives	To verify that all core functional requirements for the Member and Librarian roles are met, ensuring a stable and usable first release.

3.0 Scope	In-Scope: Functional Testing of: User Authentication, Book Search, Book Checkout (Member), Book Management - Add/Mark Lost (Librarian), Role-Based Access Control (RBAC).
Out-of-Scope: Non-Functional Testing (Performance, Security, Compatibility). *Note: A basic visual check for rendering on iOS 15+ & Android 11+ will be conducted.*

4.0 Test Strategy	Test Levels: Component & Integration Testing.
Test Types: Functional, Positive, Negative, Boundary, UI.
Test Design Techniques: Equivalence Partitioning, Boundary Value Analysis, State Transition, Error Guessing.

5.0 Entry & Exit Criteria	Entry Criteria: A stable build (v1.0.0) is deployed to the QA environment; Test data is prepared.
Exit Criteria: All test cases executed; No open Critical/High severity defects; Test Case Pass Rate â‰¥ 95%.

6.0 Defect Management	Defects will be logged in the Jira defect tracking system. They will follow the standard lifecycle: New -> Assigned -> In Progress -> Fixed -> Re-test -> Verified/Reopened -> Closed.
2. Detailed Test Case Specification

Test Case ID: TC-LIB-LOGIN-001
Module: Authentication
Description: Verify successful login with valid Member credentials.
Pre-condition: A valid Member account exists (Username: lib_member01, Password: Pass@123).

Step	Action	Expected Result	Status (Pass/Fail)
1	Launch the Library App.	Splash screen appears, then Login screen is displayed.	
2	Enter lib_member01 in the Username field.	Text is entered and masked.	
3	Enter Pass@123 in the Password field.	Text is entered and masked.	
4	Tap the "Log In" button.	User is authenticated. The app navigates to the Member Dashboard. The dashboard header displays "Welcome, Member".	

Test Case ID: TC-LIB-CHKOUT-002
Module: Book Checkout
Description: Verify system behavior when a Member attempts to check out a book with status "Checked Out".
Pre-condition: User is logged in as a Member. Book ID BKK-778 ("The Great Gatsby") has a status of "Checked Out".

Step	Action	Expected Result	Status
1	From the Member Dashboard, tap the "Search" icon.	Search screen is displayed.	
2	In the search bar, enter "The Great Gatsby".	Search results display one entry for "The Great Gatsby" with a red "Checked Out" badge.	
3	Tap on the "The Great Gatsby" result.	Book Details screen opens, showing Title, Author, and a disabled "Check Out" button. A message "This book is currently unavailable" is displayed.	
4	Attempt to tap the disabled "Check Out" button.	No action occurs. The button state remains disabled.	


